summary: An Ordinance accepting a bill of sale from the Weyerhauser Timber Company, a corporation duly organized and existing under the laws of the State of Washington, to The City of Seattle, dated December 15, 1911, to all that timber lying and being on that portion of the Northeast Quarter (NE 1/4) of the Northeast Quarter (NE 1/4) of Section Ten (10), Township Twenty-two (22) North, Range Eight (8) East, W. M., which lies north of the south bank of Cedar River in King County, State of Washington, and appropriating Two Hundred Sixty-one and 47/100 ($261.47) Dollars in payment therefor from the Cedar River Shed Condemnation Fund.
